{"word":"G868 - ἀφίστημι - aphístēmi - af-is'-tay-mee - Depart","slug":"G868","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">ἀφίστημι</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>aphístēmi"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>af-is'-tay-mee"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Depart"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03B1;&#x0313;&#x03C6;&#x03B9;&#x0301;&#x03C3;&#x03C4;&#x03B7;&#x03BC;&#x03B9; - aphiste&#x0304;mi</b> - <i>af-is'-tay-mee</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/G575\">G575</a> and <a href=\"#/G2476\">G2476</a>; to <i>remove</i>, that is, (actively) <i>instigate</i> to revolt; usually (reflexively) to <i>desist</i>, <i>desert</i>, etc.: - depart, draw (fall) away, refrain, withdraw self."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G1370\">G1370</a>, <a href=\"#/G646\">G646</a>"}]}